AllItems.Description: Allows a Pokemon whose evolution is usually triggered by trading to evolve
AllItems.Effect: The Linking Cord triggers the evolution of certain Pokmon (all of which can alternatively evolve when traded) upon use. This consumes the Linking Cord.

AllAbilities.Name: Stench
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's damaging moves have a 10% chance to make the target flinch with each hit if they do not already cause flinching as a secondary effect.

This ability does not stack with a held item.

Overworld: The wild encounter rate is halved while this Pokmon is first in the party.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 10% chance of making target Pokmon flinch with each hit.

AllAbilities.Name: Drizzle
AllAbilities.Description:
The weather changes to rain when this Pokmon enters battle and does not end unless replaced by another weather condition.

If multiple Pokmon with this ability, drought, sand stream, or snow warning are sent out at the same time, the abilities will activate in order of Speed, respecting trick room.  Each ability's weather will cancel the previous weather, and only the weather summoned by the slowest of the Pokmon will stay.
AllAbilities.Effect: Summons rain that lasts indefinitely upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Speed Boost
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon's Speed rises one stage after each turn.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises Speed one stage after each turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Battle Armor
AllAbilities.Description:
Moves cannot score critical hits against this Pokmon.

This ability functions identically to shell armor.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against critical hits.

AllAbilities.Name: Sturdy
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon is at full HP, any hit that would knock it out will instead leave it with 1 HP.  Regardless of its current HP, it is also immune to the one-hit KO moves: fissure, guillotine, horn drill, and sheer cold.

If this Pokmon is holding a focus sash, this ability takes precedence and the item will not be consumed.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents being KOed from full HP, leaving 1 HP instead.  Protects against the one-hit KO moves regardless of HP.

AllAbilities.Name: Damp
AllAbilities.Description: While this Pokmon is in battle, self destruct and explosion will fail and aftermath will not take effect.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents self destruct, explosion, and aftermath from working while the Pokmon is in battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Limber
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be paralyzed.

If a Pokmon is paralyzed and acquires this ability, its paralysis is healed; this includes when regaining a lost ability upon leaving battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents paralysis.

AllAbilities.Name: Sand Veil
AllAbilities.Description:
During a sandstorm, this Pokmon has 1.25 its evasion, and it does not take sandstorm damage regardless of type.

The evasion bonus does not count as a stat modifier.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is halved in a sandstorm.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases evasion to 1.25 during a sandstorm.  Protects against sandstorm damage.

AllAbilities.Name: Static
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, the move's user has a 30% chance of being paralyzed.

Pokmon that are immune to electric-type moves can still be paralyzed by this ability.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, there is a 50% chance that encounters will be with an electric Pokmon, if applicable.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of paralyzing attacking Pokmon on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Volt Absorb
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever an electric-type move hits this Pokmon, it heals for 1/4 of its maximum HP, negating any other effect on it.

This ability will not take effect if this Pokmon is ground-type and thus immune to Electric moves.  Electric moves will ignore this Pokmon's substitute.

This effect includes non-damaging moves, i.e. thunder wave.
AllAbilities.Effect: Absorbs electric moves, healing for 1/4 max HP.

AllAbilities.Name: Water Absorb
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a water-type move hits this Pokmon, it heals for 1/4 of its maximum HP, negating any other effect on it.

Water moves will ignore this Pokmon's substitute.
AllAbilities.Effect: Absorbs water moves, healing for 1/4 max HP.

AllAbilities.Name: Oblivious
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be infatuated and is immune to captivate.

If a Pokmon is infatuated and acquires this ability, its infatuation is cleared.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents infatuation and protects against captivate.

AllAbilities.Name: Cloud Nine
AllAbilities.Description:
While this Pokmon is in battle, weather can still be in play, but will not have any of its effects.

This ability functions identically to air lock.
AllAbilities.Effect: Negates all effects of weather, but does not prevent the weather itself.

AllAbilities.Name: Compound Eyes
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's moves have 1.3 their accuracy.

This ability has no effect on the one-hit KO moves (fissure, guillotine, horn drill, and sheer cold).

Overworld: If the first Pokmon in the party has this ability, the chance of a wild Pokmon holding a particular item is raised from 50%, 5%, or 1% to 60%, 20%, or 5%, respectively.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases moves' accuracy to 1.3.

AllAbilities.Name: Insomnia
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be asleep.

This causes rest to fail altogether.  If a Pokmon is asleep and acquires this ability, it will immediately wake up; this includes when regaining a lost ability upon leaving battle.

This ability functions identically to vital spirit in battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents sleep.

AllAbilities.Name: Color Change
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever this Pokmon takes damage from a move, the Pokmon's type changes to match the move.

If the Pokmon has two types, both are overridden.  The Pokmon must directly take damage; for example, moves blocked by a substitute will not trigger this ability, nor will moves that deal damage indirectly, such as spikes.

This ability takes effect on only the last hit of a multiple-hit attack.

In Pokmon Colosseum and XD: Gale of Darkness, this ability does not take effect on Shadow-type moves.
AllAbilities.Effect: Changes type to match when hit by a damaging move.

AllAbilities.Name: Immunity
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be poisoned.  This includes bad poison.

If a Pokmon is poisoned and acquires this ability, its poison is healed; this includes when regaining a lost ability upon leaving battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents poison.

AllAbilities.Name: Flash Fire
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is immune to fire-type moves.  Once this Pokmon has been hit by a Fire move, its own Fire moves will inflict 1.5 as much damage until it leaves battle.

This ability has no effect while the Pokmon is frozen.  The Fire damage bonus is retained even if the Pokmon is frozen and thawed or the ability is lost or disabled.  Fire moves will ignore this Pokmon's substitute.  This ability takes effect even on non-damaging moves, i.e. will o wisp.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against fire moves.  Once one has been blocked, the Pokmon's own Fire moves inflict 1.5 damage until it leaves battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Shield Dust
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is immune to the extra effects of moves used against it.

An extra effect is a move's chance, listed as an "effect chance", to inflict a status ailment, cause a stat change, or make the target flinch in addition to the move's main effect.  For example, thunder shock's paralysis is an extra effect, but thunder wave's is not, nor are knock off's item removal and air cutter's increased critical hit rate.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against incoming moves' extra effects.

AllAbilities.Name: Own Tempo
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be confused.

If a Pokmon is confused and acquires this ability, its confusion will immediately be healed.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents confusion.

AllAbilities.Name: Suction Cups
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be forced out of battle by moves such as whirlwind.

dragon tail and circle throw still inflict damage against this Pokmon.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the success rate while fishing is increased.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents being forced out of battle by other Pokmon's moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Intimidate
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon enters battle, the opponent's Attack is lowered by one stage.  In a double battle, both opponents are affected.

This ability also takes effect when acquired during a battle, but will not take effect again if lost and reobtained without leaving battle.

This ability has no effect on an opponent that has a substitute.

Overworld: If the first Pokmon in the party has this ability, any random encounter with a Pokmon five or more levels lower than it has a 50% chance of being skipped.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lowers opponents' Attack one stage upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Shadow Tag
AllAbilities.Description:
While this Pokmon is in battle, opposing Pokmon cannot flee or switch out.

Other Pokmon with this ability are unaffected.  Pokmon with run away can still flee.  Pokmon can still switch out with the use of a move or item.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents opponents from fleeing or switching out.

AllAbilities.Name: Rough Skin
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, the move's user takes 1/8 of its maximum HP in damage.

This ability functions identically to iron barbs.
AllAbilities.Effect: Damages attacking Pokmon for 1/8 their max HP on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Wonder Guard
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is immune to damaging moves that are not super effective against it.

Moves that inflict fixed damage, such as night shade or seismic toss, are considered super effective if their types are.  Damage not directly dealt by moves, such as damage from weather, a status ailment, or spikes, is not prevented.

This ability cannot be copied with role play or traded away with skill swap, but it can be copied with trace, disabled with gastro acid, or changed with worry seed.  This Pokmon can still use Role Play itself to lose this ability, but not Skill Swap.

If this Pokmon has a substitute, this ability will block moves as usual and any moves not blocked will react to the Substitute as usual.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against damaging moves that are not super effective.

AllAbilities.Name: Levitate
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is immune to ground-type moves, spikes, toxic spikes, and arena trap.

This ability is disabled during gravity or ingrain, or while holding an iron ball.  This ability is not disabled during roost.
AllAbilities.Effect: Evades ground moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Effect Spore
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, the move's user has a 30% chance of being paralyzed, poisoned, or put to sleep, chosen at random.

Nothing is done to compensate if the move's user is immune to one of these ailments; there is simply a lower chance that the move's user will be affected.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of inflcting either paralysis, poison, or sleep on attacking Pokmon on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Synchronize
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever this Pokmon is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned, the Pokmon who gave this Pokmon that ailment is also given the ailment.

This ability passes back bad poison when this Pokmon is badly poisoned.  This ability cannot pass on a status ailment that the Pokmon did not directly receive from another Pokmon, such as the poison from toxic spikes or the burn from a flame orb.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, wild Pokmon have a 50% chance of having the lead Pokmon's nature, and a 50% chance of being given a random nature as usual, including the lead Pokmon's nature.  This does not work on Pokmon received outside of battle or roaming legendaries.
AllAbilities.Effect: Copies burns, paralysis, and poison received onto the Pokmon that inflicted them.

AllAbilities.Name: Clear Body
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot have its stats lowered by other Pokmon.

This ability does not prevent any stat losses other than stat modifiers, such as the Speed cut from paralysis.  This Pokmon can still be passed negative stat modifiers through guard swap, heart swap, or power swap.

This ability functions identically to white smoke in battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents stats from being lowered by other Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Natural Cure
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is cured of any major status ailment when it is switched out for another Pokmon.

If this ability is acquired during battle, the Pokmon is cured upon leaving battle before losing the temporary ability.
AllAbilities.Effect: Cures any major status ailment upon switching out.

AllAbilities.Name: Lightning Rod
AllAbilities.Description:
All other Pokmon's single-target electric-type moves are redirected to this Pokmon if it is an eligible target.  Other Pokmon's Electric moves raise this Pokmon's Special Attack one stage, negating any other effect on it, and cannot miss it.

If the move's intended target also has this ability, the move is not redirected.  When multiple Pokmon with this ability are possible targets for redirection, the move is redirected to the one with the highest Speed stat, or, in the case of a tie, to a random tied Pokmon.  follow me takes precedence over this ability.

If the Pokmon is a ground-type and thus immune to Electric moves, its immunity prevents the Special Attack boost.
AllAbilities.Effect: Redirects single-target electric moves to this Pokmon where possible.  Absorbs Electric moves, raising Special Attack one stage.

AllAbilities.Name: Serene Grace
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's moves have twice their usual effect chance.

An effect chance is a move's chance to inflict a status ailment, cause a stat change, or make the target flinch in addition to the move's main effect.  For example, flamethrower's chance of burning the target is doubled, but protect's chance of success and air cutter's increased critical hit rate are unaffected.

secret power is unaffected.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles the chance of moves' extra effects occurring.

AllAbilities.Name: Swift Swim
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Speed is doubled during rain.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles Speed during rain.

AllAbilities.Name: Chlorophyll
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Speed is doubled during strong sunlight.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles Speed during strong sunlight.

AllAbilities.Name: Illuminate
AllAbilities.Description:
Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is doubled.

This ability has no effect in battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles the wild encounter rate.

AllAbilities.Name: Trace
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon enters battle, it copies a random opponent's ability.

This ability cannot copy flower gift, forecast, illusion, imposter, multitype, trace, wonder guard, or zen mode.
AllAbilities.Effect: Copies an opponent's ability upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Huge Power
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Attack is doubled while in battle.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.

This ability functions identically to pure power.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles Attack in battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Poison Point
AllAbilities.Description: Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, the move's user has a 30% chance of being poisoned.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of poisoning attacking Pokmon on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Inner Focus
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon cannot flinch.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents flinching.

AllAbilities.Name: Magma Armor
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be frozen.

If a Pokmon is frozen and acquires this ability, it will immediately thaw out; this includes when regaining a lost ability upon leaving battle.

Overworld: If any Pokmon in the party has this ability, each egg in the party has its hatch counter decreased by 2 (rather than 1) each step cycle, making eggs hatch roughly twice as quickly.  This effect does not stack if multiple Pokmon have this ability or flame body.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents freezing.

AllAbilities.Name: Water Veil
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be burned.

If a Pokmon is burned and acquires this ability, its burn is healed; this includes when regaining a lost ability upon leaving battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents burns.

AllAbilities.Name: Magnet Pull
AllAbilities.Description:
While this Pokmon is in battle, opposing steel-type Pokmon cannot flee or switch out.

Pokmon with run away can still flee.  Pokmon can still switch out with the use of a move or item.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, Steel-type Pokmon have a higher encounter rate.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents steel opponents from fleeing or switching out.

AllAbilities.Name: Soundproof
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is immune to moves flagged as being sound-based.

heal bell is unaffected.  uproar still prevents this Pokmon from sleeping.  This Pokmon can still receive a Perish Song counter through baton pass, and will retain a Perish Song counter if it acquires this ability after Perish Song is used.

howl, roar of time, sonic boom, and yawn are not flagged as sound-based.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against sound-based moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Rain Dish
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon heals for 1/16 of its maximum HP after each turn during rain.
AllAbilities.Effect: Heals for 1/16 max HP after each turn during rain.

AllAbilities.Name: Sand Stream
AllAbilities.Description:
The weather changes to a sandstorm when this Pokmon enters battle and does not end unless cancelled by another weather condition.

If multiple Pokmon with this ability, drizzle, drought, or snow warning are sent out at the same time, the abilities will activate in order of Speed, respecting trick room.  Each ability's weather will cancel the previous weather, and only the weather summoned by the slowest of the Pokmon will stay.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is halved in a sandstorm.
AllAbilities.Effect: Summons a sandstorm that lasts indefinitely upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Pressure
AllAbilities.Description:
Moves targetting this Pokmon use one extra PP.

This ability stacks if multiple targets have it.  This ability still affects moves that fail or miss.  This ability does not affect ally moves that target either the entire field or just its side, nor this Pokmon's self-targetted moves; it does, however, affect single-targetted ally moves aimed at this Pokmon, ally moves that target all other Pokmon, and opponents' moves that target the entire field.  If this ability raises a move's PP cost above its remaining PP, it will use all remaining PP.

When this Pokmon enters battle, all participating trainers are notified that it has this ability.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, higher-levelled Pokmon have their encounter rate increased.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases the PP cost of moves targetting the Pokmon by one.

AllAbilities.Name: Thick Fat
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon takes half as much damage from fire- and ice-type moves.
AllAbilities.Effect: Halves damage from fire and ice moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Early Bird
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's remaining sleep turn count falls by 2 rather than 1.

If this Pokmon's sleep counter is at 1, it will fall to 0 and then the Pokmon will wake up.
AllAbilities.Effect: Makes sleep pass twice as quickly.

AllAbilities.Name: Flame Body
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, the move's user has a 30% chance of being burned.

Overworld: If any Pokmon in the party has this ability, each egg in the party has its hatch counter decreased by 2 (rather than 1) each step cycle, making eggs hatch roughly twice as quickly.  This effect does not stack if multiple Pokmon have this ability or magma armor.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of burning attacking Pokmon on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Run Away
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon is always successful fleeing from wild battles, even if trapped by a move or ability.
AllAbilities.Effect: Ensures success fleeing from wild battles.

AllAbilities.Name: Keen Eye
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot have its accuracy lowered.

This ability does not prevent any accuracy losses other than stat modifiers, such as the accuracy cut from fog; nor does it prevent other Pokmon's evasion from making this Pokmon's moves less accurate.  This Pokmon can still be passed negative accuracy modifiers through heart swap.

Overworld: If the first Pokmon in the party has this ability, any random encounter with a Pokmon five or more levels lower than it has a 50% chance of being skipped.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents accuracy from being lowered.

AllAbilities.Name: Hyper Cutter
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Attack cannot be lowered by other Pokmon.

This ability does not prevent any Attack losses other than stat modifiers, such as the Attack cut from a burn.  This Pokmon can still be passed negative Attack modifiers through heart swap or power swap.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents Attack from being lowered by other Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Pickup
AllAbilities.Description:
At the end of each turn, if another Pokmon consumed or Flung a held item that turn, this Pokmon picks up the item if it is not already holding one.  After each battle, this Pokmon has a 10% chance of picking up an item if it is not already holding one.

The air balloon and eject button cannot be picked up.

The items that may be found vary by game, and, since Pokmon Emerald, by the Pokmon's level.  This ability is checked after the battle ends, at which point any temporary ability changes have worn off.
AllAbilities.Effect: Picks up other Pokmon's used and Flung held items.  May also pick up an item after battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Truant
AllAbilities.Description:
Every second turn on which this Pokmon should attempt to use a move, it will instead do nothing ("loaf around").

Loafing around interrupts moves that take multiple turns the same way paralysis, flinching, etc do.  Most such moves, for example bide or rollout, are simply cut off upon loafing around.  Attacks with a recharge turn, such as hyper beam, do not have to recharge; attacks with a preparation turn, such as fly, do not end up being used.  Moves that are forced over multiple turns and keep going through failure, such as outrage, uproar, or any move forced by encore, keep going as usual.

If this Pokmon is confused, its confusion is not checked when loafing around; the Pokmon cannot hurt itself, and its confusion does not end or come closer to ending.

If this Pokmon attempts to move but fails, e.g. because of paralysis or gravity, it still counts as having moved and will loaf around the next turn.  If it does not attempt to move, e.g. because it is asleep or frozen, whatever it would have done will be postponed until its next attempt; that is, it will either loaf around or move as usual, depending on what it last did.

This ability cannot be changed with worry seed, but it can be disabled with gastro acid, changed with role play, or traded away with skill swap.
AllAbilities.Effect: Skips every second turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Hustle
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's physical moves do 1.5 as much regular damage, but have 0.8 their usual accuracy.

Special moves are unaffected.  Moves that do set damage, such as seismic toss, have their accuracy affected, but not their damage.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, higher-levelled Pokmon have their encounter rate increased.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens physical moves to inflict 1.5 damage, but decreases their accuracy to 0.8.

AllAbilities.Name: Cute Charm
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, the move's user has a 30% chance of being infatuated.

Overworld: If the first Pokmon in the party has this ability, any wild Pokmon whose species can be either gender has a 2/3 chance of being set to the opposite gender, and a 1/3 chance of having a random gender as usual.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of infatuating attacking Pokmon on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Plus
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon has 1.5 its Special Attack if any friendly Pokmon has plus or minus.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.  If either ability is disabled by gastro acid, both lose their effect.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Special Attack to 1.5 when a friendly Pokmon has plus or minus.

AllAbilities.Name: Minus
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon has 1.5 its Special Attack if any friendly Pokmon has plus or minus.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.  If either ability is disabled by gastro acid, both lose their effect.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Special Attack to 1.5 when a friendly Pokmon has plus or minus.

AllAbilities.Name: Forecast
AllAbilities.Description:
During rain, strong sunlight, or hail, this Pokmon's type changes to water, fire, or ice, respectively, and its form changes to match.

This ability has no effect for any Pokmon other than castform.

If the weather ends or becomes anything that does not trigger this ability, or a Pokmon with air lock or cloud nine enters battle, this Pokmon's type and form revert to their default.  If this ability is lost or disabled, this Pokmon cannot change its current type and form until it regains its ability.
AllAbilities.Effect: Changes castform's type and form to match the weather.

AllAbilities.Name: Sticky Hold
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's hold item cannot be removed by other Pokmon.

Damaging moves that would remove this Pokmon's item can still inflict damage against this Pokmon, e.g. knock off or pluck.  This Pokmon can still use moves that involve the loss of its own item, e.g. fling or trick.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the encounter rate while fishing is increased.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents a held item from being removed by other Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Shed Skin
AllAbilities.Description: After each turn, this Pokmon has a 33% of being cured of any major status ailment.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 33% chance of curing any major status ailment after each turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Guts
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever this Pokmon is asleep, burned, paralyzed, or poisoned, it has 1.5 its Attack.  This Pokmon is not affected by the usual Attack cut from a burn.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Attack to 1.5 with a major status ailment.

AllAbilities.Name: Marvel Scale
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever this Pokmon has a major status ailment, it has 1.5 its Defense.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Defense to 1.5 with a major status ailment.

AllAbilities.Name: Liquid Ooze
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a Pokmon would heal after hitting this Pokmon with a leeching move like absorb, it instead loses as many HP as it would usually gain.

dream eater is unaffected.
AllAbilities.Effect: Damages opponents using leeching moves for as much as they would heal.

AllAbilities.Name: Overgrow
AllAbilities.Description: When this Pokmon has 1/3 or less of its HP remaining, its grass-type moves inflict 1.5 as much regular damage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens grass moves to inflict 1.5 damage at 1/3 max HP or less.

AllAbilities.Name: Blaze
AllAbilities.Description: When this Pokmon has 1/3 or less of its HP remaining, its fire-type moves inflict 1.5 as much regular damage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens fire moves to inflict 1.5 damage at 1/3 max HP or less.

AllAbilities.Name: Torrent
AllAbilities.Description: When this Pokmon has 1/3 or less of its HP remaining, its water-type moves inflict 1.5 as much regular damage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens water moves to inflict 1.5 damage at 1/3 max HP or less.

AllAbilities.Name: Swarm
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon has 1/3 or less of its HP remaining, its bug-type moves inflict 1.5 as much regular damage.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is increased.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens bug moves to inflict 1.5 damage at 1/3 max HP or less.

AllAbilities.Name: Rock Head
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon does not receive recoil damage from its recoil moves.

struggle's recoil is unaffected.  This ability does not prevent crash damage from missing with jump kick or high jump kick.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against recoil damage.

AllAbilities.Name: Drought
AllAbilities.Description:
The weather changes to strong sunlight when this Pokmon enters battle and does not end unless cancelled by another weather condition.

If multiple Pokmon with this ability, drizzle, sand stream, or snow warning are sent out at the same time, the abilities will activate in order of Speed, respecting trick room.  Each ability's weather will cancel the previous weather, and only the weather summoned by the slowest of the Pokmon will stay.
AllAbilities.Effect: Summons strong sunlight that lasts indefinitely upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Arena Trap
AllAbilities.Description:
While this Pokmon is in battle, opposing Pokmon cannot flee or switch out.  flying-type Pokmon and Pokmon in the air, e.g. due to levitate or magnet rise, are unaffected.

Pokmon with run away can still flee.  Pokmon can still switch out with the use of a move or item.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is doubled.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents opponents from fleeing or switching out.  Eluded by flying-types and Pokmon in the air.

AllAbilities.Name: Vital Spirit
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be asleep.

This causes rest to fail altogether.  If a Pokmon is asleep and acquires this ability, it will immediately wake up; this includes when regaining a lost ability upon leaving battle.

This ability functions identically to insomnia in battle.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, higher-levelled Pokmon have their encounter rate increased.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents sleep.

AllAbilities.Name: White Smoke
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot have its stats lowered by other Pokmon.

This ability does not prevent any stat losses other than stat modifiers, such as the Speed cut from paralysis; nor self-inflicted stat drops, such as the Special Attack drop from overheat; nor opponent-triggered stat boosts, such as the Attack boost from swagger.  This Pokmon can still be passed negative stat modifiers through guard swap, heart swap, or power swap.

This ability functions identically to clear body in battle.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is halved.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents stats from being lowered by other Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Pure Power
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Attack is doubled in battle.

This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.

This ability functions identically to huge power.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles Attack in battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Shell Armor
AllAbilities.Description:
Moves cannot score critical hits against this Pokmon.

This ability functions identically to battle armor.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against critical hits.

AllAbilities.Name: Air Lock
AllAbilities.Description:
While this Pokmon is in battle, weather can still be in play, but will not have any of its effects.

This ability functions identically to cloud nine.
AllAbilities.Effect: Negates all effects of weather, but does not prevent the weather itself.

AllAbilities.Name: Tangled Feet
AllAbilities.Description: When this Pokmon is confused, it has twice its evasion.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles evasion when confused.

AllAbilities.Name: Motor Drive
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever an electric-type move hits this Pokmon, its Speed rises one stage, negating any other effect on it.

This ability will not take effect if this Pokmon is immune to Electric moves.  Electric moves will ignore this Pokmon's substitute.

This effect includes non-damaging moves, i.e. thunder wave.
AllAbilities.Effect: Absorbs electric moves, raising Speed one stage.

AllAbilities.Name: Rivalry
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon inflicts 1.25 as much regular damage against Pokmon of the same gender and 0.75 as much regular damage against Pokmon of the opposite gender.

If either Pokmon is genderless, damage is unaffected.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases damage inflicted to 1.25 against Pokmon of the same gender, but decreases damage to 0.75 against the opposite gender.

AllAbilities.Name: Steadfast
AllAbilities.Description: Whenever this Pokmon flinches, its Speed rises one stage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises Speed one stage upon flinching.

AllAbilities.Name: Snow Cloak
AllAbilities.Description:
During hail, this Pokmon has 1.25 its evasion, and it does not take hail damage regardless of type.

The evasion bonus does not count as a stat modifier.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is halved in snow.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases evasion to 1.25 during hail.  Protects against hail damage.

AllAbilities.Name: Gluttony
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon eats any held Berry triggered by low HP when it falls below 50% of its HP, regardless of the Berry's usual threshold.
AllAbilities.Effect: Makes the Pokmon eat any held Berry triggered by low HP below 1/2 its max HP.

AllAbilities.Name: Anger Point
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever this Pokmon receives a critical hit, its Attack rises to the maximum of 6 stages.

This ability will still take effect if the critical hit is received by a substitute.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises Attack to the maximum of six stages upon receiving a critical hit.

AllAbilities.Name: Unburden
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon uses or loses its held item, its Speed is doubled.  If it gains another item or leaves battle, this bonus is lost.

This includes when the Pokmon drops its item because of knock off.  This bonus does not count as a stat modifier.  There is no notification when this ability takes effect.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles Speed upon using or losing a held item.

AllAbilities.Name: Heatproof
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon takes half as much damage from fire-type moves and burns.
AllAbilities.Effect: Halves damage from fire moves and burns.

AllAbilities.Name: Simple
AllAbilities.Description:
Each stage of this Pokmon's stat modifiers acts as two stages.  These doubled stages are still limited to a minimum of -6 and a maximum of 6.

This Pokmon can still accumulate less than -3 or more than 3 stages of stat modifiers, even though the extra ones have no effect after doubling.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles the Pokmon's stat modifiers.  These doubled modifiers are still capped at -6 or 6 stages.

AllAbilities.Name: Dry Skin
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon takes 1/8 of its maximum HP in damage after each turn during strong sunlight, but it heals for 1/8 of its HP each turn during rain.  This Pokmon takes 1.25 as much damage from fire-type moves, but whenever a water move hits it, it heals for 1/4 its maximum HP instead.
AllAbilities.Effect: Causes 1/8 max HP in damage each turn during strong sunlight, but heals for 1/8 max HP during rain.  Increases damage from fire moves to 1.25, but absorbs water moves, healing for 1/4 max HP.

AllAbilities.Name: Download
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon enters battle, its Attack or Special Attack, whichever corresponds to its opponents' weaker total defensive stat, rises one stage.  In the event of a tie, Special Attack is raised.

This ability also takes effect when acquired during a battle.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises the attack stat corresponding to the opponents' weaker defense one stage upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Iron Fist
AllAbilities.Description:
Moves flagged as being punch-based have 1.2 their base power for this Pokmon.

sucker punch is not flagged as punch-based; its original, Japanese name only means "surprise attack".
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens punch-based moves to 1.2 their power.

AllAbilities.Name: Poison Heal
AllAbilities.Description: If this Pokmon is poisoned, it will heal for 1/8 of its maximum HP after each turn rather than taking damage.  This includes bad poison.
AllAbilities.Effect: Heals for 1/8 max HP after each turn when poisoned in place of damage.

AllAbilities.Name: Adaptability
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon inflicts twice as much damage with moves whose types match its own, rather than the usual same-type attack bonus of 1.5.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases the same-type attack bonus from 1.5 to 2.

AllAbilities.Name: Skill Link
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon always hits five times with two-to-five-hit moves, such as icicle spear.  It also bypasses the accuracy checks on triple kick's second and third hits.
AllAbilities.Effect: Extends two-to-five-hit moves and triple kick to their full length every time.

AllAbilities.Name: Hydration
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon is cured of any major status ailment after each turn during rain.
AllAbilities.Effect: Cures any major status ailment after each turn during rain.

AllAbilities.Name: Solar Power
AllAbilities.Description: During strong sunlight, this Pokmon has 1.5 its Special Attack but takes 1/8 of its maximum HP in damage after each turn.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Special Attack to 1.5 but costs 1/8 max HP after each turn during strong sunlight.

AllAbilities.Name: Quick Feet
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever this Pokmon has a major status ailment, it has 1.5 its Speed.  This Pokmon is not affected by the usual Speed cut from paralysis.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is halved.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Speed to 1.5 with a major status ailment.

AllAbilities.Name: Normalize
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's moves all act as if they were normal-type.

Moves that inflict typeless damage do so as usual.  Moves of variable type, such as hidden power, are affected.  They otherwise work as usual, however; weather ball, for example, is always forced to be Normal, but it still has doubled power and looks different during weather.

As thunder wave is prevented by immunities, unlike most non-damaging moves, it does not affect ghost-type Pokmon under the effect of this ability.
AllAbilities.Effect: Makes the Pokmon's moves all act normal-type.

AllAbilities.Name: Sniper
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon inflicts triple damage with critical hits, rather than the usual double damage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens critical hits to inflict 3 damage rather than 2.

AllAbilities.Name: Magic Guard
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon is immune to damage not directly caused by a move.

For example, this Pokmon takes no damage from from weather, recoil, status ailments, or spikes, but it still suffers from the Attack cut when burned, and a life orb will still power up this Pokmon's moves without damaging it.  Anything that directly depends on such damage will also not happen; for example, leech seed will neither hurt this Pokmon nor heal the opponent, and Pokmon with a jaboca berry or rowap berry will not consume the berry when hit by this Pokmon.

The following are unaffected: struggle, pain split (whether used by or against this Pokmon), belly drum, substitute, curse, moves that knock the user out, and damage from confusion.

This Pokmon will neither lose nor regain HP if it drains HP from a Pokmon with liquid ooze.

If this Pokmon is badly poisoned, the poison counter is still increased each turn; if the Pokmon loses this ability, it will begin taking as much damage as it would be if it had been taking increasing damage each turn.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against damage not directly caused by a move.

AllAbilities.Name: No Guard
AllAbilities.Description:
Moves used by or against this Pokmon never miss.

One-hit KO moves are unaffected.  Moves affected by this ability can hit Pokmon during the preparation turn of moves like dig or fly.

Overworld: If the lead Pokmon has this ability, the wild encounter rate is doubled.
AllAbilities.Effect: Ensures all moves used by and against the Pokmon hit.

AllAbilities.Name: Stall
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon moves last within its priority bracket.

Multiple Pokmon with this ability move in order of Speed amongst themselves.

The full incense and lagging tail take precedence over this ability; that is, Pokmon with these items move after Pokmon with this ability.  Pokmon with both this ability and one of these items are delayed as much as if they had only the item.

This ability works as usual during trick room: Pokmon with this ability will move in reverse order of Speed after Pokmon without it.
AllAbilities.Effect: Makes the Pokmon move last within its move's priority bracket.

AllAbilities.Name: Technician
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's moves have 1.5 their power if their base power is 60 or less.

This includes moves of variable power, such as hidden power and magnitude, when their power is 60 or less.  helping hand's power boost is taken into account for any move, as is defense curl's power boost for rollout.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens moves of 60 base power or less to 1.5 their power.

AllAbilities.Name: Leaf Guard
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon cannot be given a major status ailment during strong sunlight.

This ability does not heal prior status ailments.  rest will fail altogether with this ability in effect.  yawn will immediately fail if used on this Pokmon during strong sunlight, and an already-used Yawn will fail if the weather turns to strong sunlight in the meantime.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against major status ailments during strong sunlight.

AllAbilities.Name: Klutz
AllAbilities.Description:
In battle, this Pokmon cannot use its held item, nor will the item have any passive effect on the battle, positive or negative.  This Pokmon also cannot use fling.

The Speed cut from the iron ball and the effort items (the macho brace, power weight, power bracer, power belt, power lens, power band, and power anklet) is unaffected.  Items that do not directly affect the battle, such as the exp share, the amulet coin, or the soothe bell, work as usual.  All held items work as usual out of battle.

Other moves that use the held item, such as natural gift and switcheroo, work as usual.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents the Pokmon from using its held item in battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Mold Breaker
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's moves completely ignore abilities that could hinder or prevent their effect on the target.

For example, this Pokmon's moves ignore abilities that would fully negate them, such as water absorb; abilities that would prevent any of their effects, such as clear body, shell armor, or sticky hold; and abilities that grant any general protective benefit, such as simple, snow cloak, or thick fat.  If an ability could either hinder or help this Pokmon's moves, e.g. dry skin or unaware, the ability is ignored either way.

Abilities that do not fit this description, even if they could hinder moves in some other way, are not affected.  For example, cursed body only affects potential future uses of the move, while liquid ooze and shadow tag can only hinder a move's effect on the user.  This ablity cannot ignore type or form changes granted by abilities, for example color change or forecast; nor effects that were caused by abilities but are no longer tied to an ability, such as the rain from drizzle.  This ability cannot ignore multitype at all.

An ability ignored by this ability is only nullified while the move is being used.  For example, this Pokmon's moves can paralyze a Pokmon with limber, but Limber will activate and heal the paralysis immediately thereafter, and this Pokmon's spikes are not affected by this ability after they have been placed.

When this Pokmon enters battle, all participating trainers are notified that it has this ability.

This ability functions identically to teravolt and turboblaze.
AllAbilities.Effect: Bypasses targets' abilities if they could hinder or prevent a move.

AllAbilities.Name: Super Luck
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon's moves have critical hit rates one stage higher than normal.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises moves' critical hit rates one stage.

AllAbilities.Name: Aftermath
AllAbilities.Description: When this Pokmon is knocked out by a move that makes contact, the move's user takes 1/4 its maximum HP in damage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Damages the attacker for 1/4 its max HP when knocked out by a contact move.

AllAbilities.Name: Anticipation
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon enters battle, if one of its opponents has a move that is super effective against it, self destruct, explosion, or a one-hit knockout move, all participating trainers are notified.

The move itself is not revealed; only that there is such a move.  Moves that inflict typeless damage, such as future sight, and moves of variable type, such as hidden power, count as their listed types.  counter, metal burst, mirror coat, and one-hit KO moves to which this Pokmon is immune do not trigger this ability.
AllAbilities.Effect: Notifies all trainers upon entering battle if an opponent has a super-effective move, self destruct, explosion, or a one-hit KO move.

AllAbilities.Name: Forewarn
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon enters battle, it reveals the move with the highest base power known by any opposing Pokmon to all participating trainers.

In the event of a tie, one is chosen at random.

Moves without a listed base power are assigned one as follows:

Power | Moves
----: | -----
  160 | One-hit KO moves: fissure, guillotine, horn drill, and sheer cold
  120 | Counter moves: counter, metal burst, and mirror coat
   80 | Variable power or set damage: crush grip, dragon rage, electro ball, endeavor, final gambit, flail, frustration, grass knot, gyro ball, heat crash, heavy slam, hidden power, low kick, natural gift, night shade, psywave, return, reversal, seismic toss, sonic boom, trump card, and wring out
    0 | Any such move not listed
AllAbilities.Effect: Reveals the opponents' strongest move upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Unaware
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon ignores other Pokmon's stat modifiers for the purposes of damage and accuracy calculation.

Effectively, this affects modifiers of every stat except Speed.

The power of punishment and stored power is calculated as usual.  When this Pokmon hurts itself in confusion, its stat modifiers affect damage as usual.
AllAbilities.Effect: Ignores other Pokmon's stat modifiers for damage and accuracy calculation.

AllAbilities.Name: Tinted Lens
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon deals twice as much damage with moves that are not very effective against the target.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles damage inflicted with not-very-effective moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Filter
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon takes 0.75 as much damage from moves that are super effective against it.

This ability functions identically to solid rock.
AllAbilities.Effect: Decreases damage taken from super-effective moves by 1/4.

AllAbilities.Name: Slow Start
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Attack and Speed are halved for five turns upon entering battle.

This ability also takes effect when acquired during battle.  If this Pokmon loses its ability before the five turns are up, its Attack and Speed return to normal; if it then regains this ability without leaving battle, its Attack and Speed are halved again, but the counter keeps counting from where it was.
AllAbilities.Effect: Halves Attack and Speed for five turns upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Scrappy
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon ignores ghost-type Pokmon's immunity to normal- and fighting-type moves.

Ghost Pokmon's other types affect damage as usual.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lets the Pokmon's normal and fighting moves hit ghost Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Storm Drain
AllAbilities.Description:
All other Pokmon's single-target water-type moves are redirected to this Pokmon, if it is an eligible target.  Other Pokmon's Water moves raise this Pokmon's Special Attack one stage, negating any other effect on it, and cannot miss it.

If the move's intended target also has this ability, the move is not redirected.  When multiple Pokmon with this ability are possible targets for redirection, the move is redirected to the one with the highest Speed stat, or, in the case of a tie, to a random tied Pokmon.  follow me takes precedence over this ability.
AllAbilities.Effect: Redirects single-target water moves to this Pokmon where possible.  Absorbs Water moves, raising Special Attack one stage.

AllAbilities.Name: Ice Body
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon heals for 1/16 of its maximum HP after each turn during hail, and it does not take hail damage regardless of type.
AllAbilities.Effect: Heals for 1/16 max HP after each turn during hail.  Protects against hail damage.

AllAbilities.Name: Solid Rock
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon takes 0.75 as much damage from moves that are super effective against it.

This ability functions identically to filter.
AllAbilities.Effect: Decreases damage taken from super-effective moves by 1/4.

AllAbilities.Name: Snow Warning
AllAbilities.Description:
The weather changes to hail when this Pokmon enters battle and does not end unless cancelled by another weather condition.

If multiple Pokmon with this ability, drizzle, drought, or sand stream are sent out at the same time, the abilities will activate in order of Speed, respecting trick room.  Each ability's weather will cancel the previous weather, and only the weather summoned by the slowest of the Pokmon will stay.
AllAbilities.Effect: Summons hail that lasts indefinitely upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Honey Gather
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon has a chance of picking up honey after each battle.  This chance starts at 5% and rises another 5% after every tenth level: 5% from level 110, 10% from 1120, and so on, up to 50% from 91100.

This ability is checked after the battle ends, at which point any temporary ability changes have worn off.
AllAbilities.Effect: The Pokmon may pick up honey after battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Frisk
AllAbilities.Description:
When this Pokmon enters battle, it reveals an opposing Pokmon's held item to all participating trainers.

In a double battle, if one opponent has an item, this Pokmon will Frisk that Pokmon; if both have an item, it will Frisk one at random.
AllAbilities.Effect: Reveals an opponent's held item upon entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Reckless
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's recoil moves and crash moves have 1.2 their base power.

struggle is unaffected.

The "crash moves" are the moves that damage the user upon missing: jump kick and high jump kick.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens recoil moves to 1.2 their power.

AllAbilities.Name: Multitype
AllAbilities.Description:
If this Pokmon is holding an elemental Plate, its type and form change to match the Plate.

This Pokmon's held item, whether or not it is a Plate, cannot be taken by covet or thief, nor removed by knock off, nor traded by switcheroo or trick.  Covet, Thief, and Knock Off still inflict damage against this Pokmon.  Unlike with sticky hold, this Pokmon cannot use fling, Switcheroo, or Trick to lose its item itself, nor gain an item through Switcheroo or Trick if it does not have one.

This ability has no effect for any Pokmon other than arceus.  This ability cannot be traded with skill swap, nor copied with role play or trace, nor disabled with gastro acid, nor changed with worry seed.  This Pokmon cannot use Skill Swap or Role Play to lose its ability itself.  mold breaker cannot ignore this ability.

If a Pokmon Transforms into an Arceus with this ability, it will Transform into Arceus's default, normal-type form.  If the Transforming Pokmon is holding a Plate, this ability will then activate and change the Pokmon into the corresponding form.
AllAbilities.Effect: Changes arceus's type and form to match its held Plate.

AllAbilities.Name: Flower Gift
AllAbilities.Description:
Friendly Pokmon have 1.5 their Attack and Special Defense during strong sunlight if any friendly Pokmon has this ability.

Unlike forecast, multitype, and zen mode, this ability is not tied to its Pokmon's form change; cherrim will switch between its forms even if it loses this ability.  As such, this ability also works if obtained by a Pokmon other than Cherrim.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases friendly Pokmon's Attack and Special Defense to 1.5 during strong sunlight.

AllAbilities.Name: Bad Dreams
AllAbilities.Description: Opposing Pokmon take 1/8 of their maximum HP in damage after each turn while they are asleep.
AllAbilities.Effect: Damages sleeping opponents for 1/8 their max HP after each turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Pickpocket
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a move makes contact with this Pokmon, if it does not have a held item, it steals the attacker's held item.

This Pokmon cannot steal upon being knocked out.  It can steal if the attacker has a substitute, but cannot steal when its own Substitute is hit.  If a move hits multiple times, only the last hit triggers this ability.  If this Pokmon is wild, it cannot steal from a trained Pokmon.
AllAbilities.Effect: Steals attacking Pokmon's held items on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Sheer Force
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's moves with extra effects have 1.3 their power, but lose their extra effects.

An effect chance is a move's chance to inflict a status ailment, cause a stat change, or make the target flinch in addition to the move's main effect. For example, thunder shock's paralysis is an extra effect, but thunder wave's is not, nor are knock off's item removal and air cutter's increased critical hit rate.

Moves that lower the user's stats are unaffected.
AllAbilities.Effect: Strengthens moves with extra effects to 1.3 their power, but prevents their extra effects.

AllAbilities.Name: Contrary
AllAbilities.Description: Whenever this Pokmon's stats would be raised, they are instead lowered by the same amount, and vice versa.
AllAbilities.Effect: Inverts stat changes.

AllAbilities.Name: Unnerve
AllAbilities.Description:
Opposing Pokmon cannot eat held Berries while this Pokmon is in battle.

Affected Pokmon can still use bug bite or pluck to eat a target's Berry.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents opposing Pokmon from eating held Berries.

AllAbilities.Name: Defiant
AllAbilities.Description:
When any of this Pokmon's stats are lowered, its Attack rises by two stages.

If multiple stats are lowered at once, this ability takes effect with each stat lowered.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises Attack two stages upon having any stat lowered.

AllAbilities.Name: Defeatist
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon's Attack and Special Attack are halved when it has half its HP or less.
AllAbilities.Effect: Halves Attack and Special Attack at 50% max HP or less.

AllAbilities.Name: Cursed Body
AllAbilities.Description: Moves that hit this Pokmon have a 30% chance of being Disabled afterward.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of Disabling any move that hits the Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Healer
AllAbilities.Description: Friendly Pokmon next to this Pokmon in double and triple battles each have a 30% chance of being cured of any major status ailment after each turn.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of curing each adjacent ally of any major status ailment after each turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Friend Guard
AllAbilities.Description:
All friendly Pokmon take 0.75 as much direct damage from moves while this Pokmon is in battle.

This effect stacks if multiple allied Pokmon have it.
AllAbilities.Effect: Decreases all direct damage taken by friendly Pokmon to 0.75.

AllAbilities.Name: Weak Armor
AllAbilities.Description:
Whenever a physical move hits this Pokmon, its Speed rises one stage and its Defense falls one stage.

This ability triggers on every hit of a multiple-hit move.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises Speed and lowers Defense by one stage each upon being hit by a physical move.

AllAbilities.Name: Heavy Metal
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon has double the usual weight for its species.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles the Pokmon's weight.

AllAbilities.Name: Light Metal
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon has half the usual weight for its species.
AllAbilities.Effect: Halves the Pokmon's weight.

AllAbilities.Name: Multiscale
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon takes half as much damage when it is hit having full HP.
AllAbilities.Effect: Halves damage taken from full HP.

AllAbilities.Name: Toxic Boost
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon has 1.5 its Attack when poisoned.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Attack to 1.5 when poisoned.

AllAbilities.Name: Flare Boost
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon has 1.5 its Special Attack when burned.
AllAbilities.Effect: Increases Special Attack to 1.5 when burned.

AllAbilities.Name: Harvest
AllAbilities.Description: After each turn, if the last item this Pokmon consumed was a Berry and it is not currently holding an item, it has a 50% chance of regaining that Berry, or a 100% chance during strong sunlight.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 50% chance of restoring a used Berry after each turn if the Pokmon has held no items in the meantime.

AllAbilities.Name: Telepathy
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon does not take damage from friendly Pokmon's moves, including single-target moves aimed at it.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against friendly Pokmon's damaging moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Moody
AllAbilities.Description:
After each turn, one of this Pokmon's stats at random rises two stages, and another falls one stage.

If a stat is already at 6 or -6 stages, it will not be chosen to be increased or decreased, respectively.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises a random stat two stages and lowers another one stage after each turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Overcoat
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon does not take damage from weather.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against damage from weather.

AllAbilities.Name: Poison Touch
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's contact moves have a 30% chance of poisoning the target with each hit.

This counts as an extra effect for the purposes of shield dust.  This ability takes effect before mummy.
AllAbilities.Effect: Has a 30% chance of poisoning target Pokmon upon contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Regenerator
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon regains 1/3 of its maximum HP when it is switched out for another Pokmon under any circumstances other than having fainted.

This ability does not take effect when a battle ends.
AllAbilities.Effect: Heals for 1/3 max HP upon switching out.

AllAbilities.Name: Big Pecks
AllAbilities.Description:
This Pokmon's Defense cannot be lowered by other Pokmon.

This Pokmon can still be passed negative Defense modifiers through heart swap or guard swap.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects against Defense drops.

AllAbilities.Name: Sand Rush
AllAbilities.Description: This Pokmon's Speed is doubled during a sandstorm, and it does not take sandstorm damage, regardless of type.
AllAbilities.Effect: Doubles Speed during a sandstorm.  Protects against sandstorm damage.

AllAbilities.Name: Wonder Skin
AllAbilities.Description: Non-damaging moves have exactly 50% base accuracy against this Pokmon.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lowers incoming non-damaging moves' base accuracy to exactly 50%.

AllAbilities.Name: Screen Cleaner
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, the effects of Light Screen, Reflect, and Aurora Veil are nullified for both opposing and ally Pokmon.
AllAbilities.Effect: Nullifies effects of Light Screen, Reflect, and Aurora Veil.

AllAbilities.Name: Steely Spirit
AllAbilities.Description: Powers up the Steel-type moves of the Pokmon and its allies.
AllAbilities.Effect: Powers up ally Pokmon's Steel-type moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Perish Body
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon with Perish Body is hit with a contact move, both the attacker and the Pokmon with Perish Body will faint in three turns.
AllAbilities.Effect: When hit by a move that makes direct contact, the Pokmon and the attacker will faint after three turns unless they switch out of battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Wandering Spirit
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon exchanges Abilities with a Pokmon that hits it with a move that makes direct contact.
AllAbilities.Effect: Swaps abilities with opponents on contact.

AllAbilities.Name: Gorilla Tactics
AllAbilities.Description: Boosts the Pokmons Attack stat but only allows the use of the first selected move.
AllAbilities.Effect: Boosts the Pokmon's Attack stat but only allows the use of the first selected move.

AllAbilities.Name: Neutralizing Gas
AllAbilities.Description: While the Pokmon is in the battle, the effects of all other Pokmons Abilities will be nullified or will not be triggered.
AllAbilities.Effect: Neutralizes abilities of all Pokmon in battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Pastel Veil
AllAbilities.Description: Prevents the Pokmon and its teammates from being poisoned. It also cures teammates of poisoning when it enters the battlefield.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents the Pokmon and its allies from being poisoned.

AllAbilities.Name: Hunger Switch
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon changes its form, alternating between its Full Belly Mode and Hangry Mode after the end of every turn.
AllAbilities.Effect: Causes Morpeko to change its form each turn, alternating between Full Belly Mode and Hangry Mode

AllAbilities.Name: Quick Draw
AllAbilities.Description: If a Pokmon with this Ability selects a damaging move, it has a 30% chance of going first in its priority bracket.
AllAbilities.Effect: Enables the Pokmon to move first occasionally.

AllAbilities.Name: Unseen Fist
AllAbilities.Description: If the Pokmon uses moves that make direct contact, it can attack the target even if the target protects itself.
AllAbilities.Effect: Contact moves can strike through Protect/Detect.

AllAbilities.Name: Curious Medicine
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, it scatters medicine from its shell, which removes all stat changes from allies.
AllAbilities.Effect: Resets all stat changes upon entering battlefield.

AllAbilities.Name: Transistor
AllAbilities.Description: Increases the power of Electric-type moves used by this Pokmon by 50%.
AllAbilities.Effect: Powers up Electric-type moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Dragons Maw
AllAbilities.Description: Increases the power of Dragon-type moves used by this Pokmon by 50%.
AllAbilities.Effect: Powers up Dragon-type moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Chilling Neigh
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon knocks out a target, it utters a chilling neigh, which boosts its Attack stat.
AllAbilities.Effect: Boosts Attack after knocking out a Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Grim Neigh
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon knocks out a target, it utters a terrifying neigh, which boosts its Sp. Atk stat.
AllAbilities.Effect: Boosts Special Attack after knocking out a Pokmon.

AllAbilities.Name: Lingering Aroma
AllAbilities.Description: Contact with the Pokmon changes the attackers Ability to Lingering Aroma.
AllAbilities.Effect: Contact changes the attacker's Ability to Lingering Aroma.

AllAbilities.Name: Seed Sower
AllAbilities.Description: Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokmon is hit by an attack.
AllAbilities.Effect: Turns the ground into Grassy Terrain when the Pokmon is hit by an attack.

AllAbilities.Name: Thermal Exchange
AllAbilities.Description: Boosts the Attack stat when the Pokmon is hit by a Fire-type move. The Pokmon also cannot be burned.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises Attack when hit by a Fire-type move. Cannot be burned.

AllAbilities.Name: Anger Shell
AllAbilities.Description: When an attack causes its HP to drop to half or less, the Pokmon gets angry. This lowers its Defense and Sp. Def stats but boosts its Attack, Sp. Atk, and Speed stats.
AllAbilities.Effect: When the Pokmon's HP drops below half, Anger Shell lowers its Defense and Special Defense but its Attack, Special Attack and Speed are raised.

AllAbilities.Name: Purifying Salt
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmons pure salt protects it from status conditions and halves the damage taken from Ghost-type moves.
AllAbilities.Effect: Protects from status conditions and halves damage from Ghost-type moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Well Baked Body
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon takes no damage when hit by Fire-type moves. Instead, its Defense stat is sharply boosted.
AllAbilities.Effect: Immune to Fire-type moves, and Defense is sharply boosted.

AllAbilities.Name: Wind Rider
AllAbilities.Description: Boosts the Pokmons Attack stat if Tailwind takes effect or if the Pokmon is hit by a wind move. The Pokmon also takes no damage from wind moves.
AllAbilities.Effect: Gives immunity to wind moves, and causes the Pokmon's Attack to increase by one stage when hit by one.

AllAbilities.Name: Guard Dog
AllAbilities.Description: Boosts the Pokmons Attack stat if intimidated. Moves and items that would force the Pokmon to switch out also fail to work.
AllAbilities.Effect: Boosts Attack if intimidated, and prevents being forced to switch out.

AllAbilities.Name: Rocky Payload
AllAbilities.Description: Increases the power of Rock-type moves used by this Pokmon by 50%.
AllAbilities.Effect: Powers up Rock-type moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Wind Power
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon becomes charged when it is hit by a wind move, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move the Pokmon uses.
AllAbilities.Effect: When hit by a wind move, the power of the next Electric-type move it uses is doubled.

AllAbilities.Name: Zero To Hero
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon transforms into its Hero Form when it switches out.
AllAbilities.Effect: Transforms into its Hero Form when switching out.

AllAbilities.Name: Commander
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, it goes inside the mouth of an ally Dondozo if one is on the field. The Pokmon then issues commands from there.
AllAbilities.Effect: Goes inside the mouth of an ally Dondozo if one is on the field.

AllAbilities.Name: Electromorphosis
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon becomes charged when it takes damage, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move the Pokmon uses.
AllAbilities.Effect: When hit by an attack, the power of the next Electric-type move it uses is doubled.

AllAbilities.Name: Protosynthesis
AllAbilities.Description: Boosts the Pokmons most proficient stat in harsh sunlight or if the Pokmon is holding Booster Energy.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises highest stat in harsh sunlight, or if holding Booster Energy.

AllAbilities.Name: Quark Drive
AllAbilities.Description: Boosts the Pokmons most proficient stat on Electric Terrain or if the Pokmon is holding Booster Energy.
AllAbilities.Effect: Raises highest stat on Electric Terrain, or if holding Booster Energy.

AllAbilities.Name: Good As Gold
AllAbilities.Description: A body of pure, solid gold gives the Pokmon full immunity to other Pokmons status moves.
AllAbilities.Effect: Gives immunity to status moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Vessel Of Ruin
AllAbilities.Description: The power of the Pokmons ruinous vessel lowers the Sp. Atk stats of all Pokmon except itself.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lowers Special Attack of all Pokmon except itself.

AllAbilities.Name: Sword Of Ruin
AllAbilities.Description: The power of the Pokmons ruinous sword lowers the Defense stats of all Pokmon except itself.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lowers Defense of all Pokmon except itself.

AllAbilities.Name: Tablets Of Ruin
AllAbilities.Description: The power of the Pokmons ruinous wooden tablets lowers the Attack stats of all Pokmon except itself.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lowers Attack of all Pokmon except itself.

AllAbilities.Name: Beads Of Ruin
AllAbilities.Description: The power of the Pokmons ruinous beads lowers the Sp. Def stats of all Pokmon except itself.
AllAbilities.Effect: Lowers Special Defense of all Pokmon except itself.

AllAbilities.Name: Orichalcum Pulse
AllAbilities.Description: Turns the sunlight harsh when the Pokmon enters a battle. The ancient pulse thrumming through the Pokmon also boosts its Attack stat in harsh sunlight.
AllAbilities.Effect: Turns the sunlight harsh when entering battle, and boosts Attack while active.

AllAbilities.Name: Hadron Engine
AllAbilities.Description: Turns the ground into Electric Terrain when the Pokmon enters a battle. The futuristic engine within the Pokmon also boosts its Sp. Atk stat on Electric Terrain.
AllAbilities.Effect: Creates an Electric Terrain when entering battle, and boosts Special Attack while active.

AllAbilities.Name: Opportunist
AllAbilities.Description: If an opponents stat is boosted, the Pokmon seizes the opportunity to boost the same stat for itself.
AllAbilities.Effect: Copies stat boosts by the opponent.

AllAbilities.Name: Cud Chew
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon eats a Berry, it will regurgitate that Berry at the end of the next turn and eat it one more time.
AllAbilities.Effect: Causes the Pokmon to reuse an already consumed Berry at the end of the next turn.

AllAbilities.Name: Sharpness
AllAbilities.Description: Increases the power of all 'slicing' moves by 50%.
AllAbilities.Effect: Powers up slicing moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Supreme Overlord
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, its Attack and Sp. Atk stats are slightly boosted for each of the allies in its party that have already been defeated.
AllAbilities.Effect: Attack and Special Attack are boosted for each party Pokmon that has been defeated.

AllAbilities.Name: Costar
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, it copies an allys stat changes.
AllAbilities.Effect: Copies ally's stat changes on entering battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Toxic Debris
AllAbilities.Description: Scatters poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team when the Pokmon takes damage from physical moves.
AllAbilities.Effect: Scatters poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team when the Pokmon takes damage from physical moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Armor Tail
AllAbilities.Description: The mysterious tail covering the Pokmons head makes opponents unable to use priority moves against the Pokmon or its allies.
AllAbilities.Effect: Prevents the opponent from using any moves that have priority, such as Quick Attack.

AllAbilities.Name: Earth Eater
AllAbilities.Description: If hit by a Ground-type move, the Pokmon has its HP restored instead of taking damage.
AllAbilities.Effect: Restores HP when hit by a Ground-type move.

AllAbilities.Name: Mycelium Might
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmon will always act more slowly when using status moves, but these moves will be unimpeded by the Ability of the target.
AllAbilities.Effect: Status moves go last, but are not affected by the opponent's ability.

AllAbilities.Name: Minds Eye
AllAbilities.Description: Mind's Eye enables the Pokmon with this Ability to hit Ghost-type Pokmon with damage-dealing Normal- and Fighting-type moves. It also prevents other Pokmon from lowering the Pokmon's accuracy and ignores changes to the opponents' evasion.
AllAbilities.Effect: The Pokmon ignores changes to opponents' evasiveness, its accuracy can't be lowered, and it can hit Ghost types with Normal- and Fighting-type moves.

AllAbilities.Name: Supersweet Syrup
AllAbilities.Description: A sickly sweet scent spreads across the field the first time the Pokmon enters a battle, lowering the evasiveness of opposing Pokmon.
AllAbilities.Effect: Once per battle, when a Pokmon with Supersweet Syrup enters the battle, it lowers the evasion stat of all adjacent opponents by one stage.

AllAbilities.Name: Hospitality
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, it showers its ally with hospitality, restoring a small amount of the ally's HP.
AllAbilities.Effect: When a Pokmon with Hospitality enters a battle, it restores HP for an ally by 25%.

AllAbilities.Name: Toxic Chain
AllAbilities.Description: The power of the Pokmon's toxic chain may badly poison any target the Pokmon hits with a move.
AllAbilities.Effect: May cause bad poisoning when the Pokmon hits an opponent with a move.

AllAbilities.Name: Embody Aspect
AllAbilities.Description: Embody Aspect boosts a particular stat, depending on the form of a Terastallized Ogerpon
AllAbilities.Effect: Embody Aspect boosts a particular stat, depending on the form of a Terastallized Ogerpon

AllAbilities.Name: Tera Shift
AllAbilities.Description: When the Pokmon enters a battle, it absorbs the energy around itself and transforms into its Terastal Form.
AllAbilities.Effect: When Terapagos enters the battle, it turns into its Terastal Form until the end of the battle.

AllAbilities.Name: Tera Shell
AllAbilities.Description: The Pokmons shell contains the powers of each type. All damage-dealing moves that hit the Pokmon when its HP is full will not be very effective.
AllAbilities.Effect: All damage-dealing moves that hit the Pokmon when its HP is full will not be very effective.

AllAbilities.Name: Teraform Zero
AllAbilities.Description: When Terapagos changes into its Stellar Form, it uses its hidden powers to eliminate all effects of weather and terrain, reducing them to zero.
AllAbilities.Effect: As soon as Terapagos assumes its Stellar Form, it will immediately neutralize weather and terrain effects.

AllAbilities.Name: Poison Puppeteer
AllAbilities.Description: When a Pokmon is poisoned by any of Pecharunt's moves, it will also become confused.
AllAbilities.Effect: Pokmon poisoned by Pecharunt's moves will also become confused.
